    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of what the plan covers:\n\n## `uv cache stats` — Implementation Plan\n\n**7 files to touch, 2 new files to create.**\n\n### What I found\n- `uv cache size` uses `diskus::DiskUsage` to scan the whole cache root and prints one number\n- The `CacheBucket` enum has 11 buckets with versioned dir names (e.g. `wheels-v6`, `sdists-v9`) and a `Display` impl via `to_str()`\n- `CacheBucket::iter()` **omits `Python`** — the plan adds it\n- `PreviewFeature::CacheSize` already gates `cache size`; `cache stats` will share the same flag\n- `cache.bucket(b)` returns the `PathBuf` for any bucket\n\n### Key changes\n1. **`crates/uv-cache/src/lib.rs`** — Add `Python` to `CacheBucket::iter()`\n2. **`crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`** — Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` variant + `StatsArgs { human: bool }` struct\n3. **`crates/uv/src/lib.rs`** — Add dispatch arm for `CacheCommand::Stats`\n4. **`crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`** *(new)* — Iterate all buckets, `DiskUsage` each path, print left-aligned table + `Total` row\n5. **`crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`** — Declare module + re-export\n6. **`crates/uv-test/src/lib.rs`** — Add `cache_stats()` builder + `with_filtered_cache_stats()` filter\n7. **`crates/uv/tests/it/cache_stats.rs`** *(new)* + `main.rs` — 3 integration tests (empty, raw, human)\n\n### Output shape\n```\nwheels-v6                11.8 MiB\nsdists-v9                96.5 KiB\n...\nTotal                    13.9 MiB\n```",
